headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 27 points and 12 rebounds and the Boston Celtics won their fourth straight game, outlasting the short-handed Toronto Raptors 132-125 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 27, Celtics outlast depleted Raptors 132-125

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 33 points and the Washington Wizards pushed ahead with a late run to beat the Los Angeles Clippers 119-117 after All-Star Paul George was a late scratch Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards beat Clippers 119-117 behind 33 from Beal

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle capped his All-Star first half with 27 points, 16 rebounds and seven assists, sending the New York Knicks into the break with a winning record after a 114-104 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Knicks reach break over .500, beat Pistons 114-104

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. scored 24 points and Nikola Jokic added 24 points, 12 rebounds and eight assists Thursday night, leading the Denver Nuggets past the Indiana Pacers 113-103.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets close out 1st half with 113-103 win at Indiana

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday hit a baseline jumper with two seconds remaining and the Milwaukee Bucks escaped with a 112-111 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Thursday night in the final game for both teams before the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holiday' hits baseline jumper to lift Bucks past Grizzlies

events.name: Miami Heat at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler had 29 points and nine assists, and the Miami Heat took advantage of Zion Williamson's absence to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 103-93 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler takes over, Heat top Pelicans 103-93

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 33 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied in the second half to beat the San Antonio Spurs 107-102 on Thursday night and snap a two-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander has 33, helps Thunder rally past Spurs

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 44 points, including 10 straight at a key moment down the stretch, to give the Portland Trail Blazers a 123-119 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has 44 and Blazers down Kings 123-119

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Cameron Payne scored 17 points, Devin Booker added 16 and the Phoenix Suns easily handled the short-handed Golden State Warriors 120-98 on Thursday night.
